        {
          "type": "thinking",
          "thinking": "Now I can analyze this more carefully:\n\n1. The policy (第十一条 of 01_expense_reimbursement_2025.md) says:\n   - 同一员工、同一费用类型在7天内出现2笔及以上报销,且合计金额达到《授权管理办法》附件二较高审批线的,应重点核查拆分规避审批。\n\n2. \"较高审批线\" - Looking at the authorization management appendix:\n   - AR-01: 0~3000\n   - AR-02: 3000~10000\n   - AR-03: 10000~50000\n   - AR-04: 50000~200000\n   - AR-05: >=200000\n\n   \"较高审批线\" - I think this refers to the tier that requires higher-level approval. For a department manager (D1 level, 部门经理), the regular approval would be AR-01 or AR-02. If the total amount triggers AR-03 (requiring 部门总经理) or above, that would be \"较高审批线\".\n\n3. Let me check the employee details for E0008 to understand their level:\n   - Employee E0008: 杨丹, level D1, position 部门经理, department 合规风控部\n\n4. Each individual expense is 3400.0:\n   - 3400 < 10000, so each individual record only needs AR-02 level approval (部门经理 + 财务复核)\n   \n5. But the total of all 3 expenses = 3400 * 3 = 10200\n   - 10200 >= 10000, so the total would trigger AR-03 (需要部门总经理审批)\n   \n   If these were submitted as one combined expense of 10200, it would require AR-03 approval (部门总经理).\n   But by splitting into 3 x 3400, each falls under AR-02, which only needs 部门经理 approval.\n\n   And indeed looking at R004209's approvals - it was approved with tier_id AR-02 by employee E0008 (who is both the employee AND the approver as 部门经理!). This is very suspicious.\n\n6. So the three records R004209, R004210, R004211 represent a classic split reimbursement scheme.\n\nLet me also check if there are other records with similar patterns. Let me look at the other records more carefully.\n\nLet me also check the approval chain for R004210 and R004211.",
          "signature": ""
        },
